      "narrative": "# CORRUPTION BRIEF: Boeing Company (BA)\n**Date of Signal: May 6, 2026 | Amount Flagged: $22.4B | Score: 95/100**\n\n---\n\nBoeing received two NASA contracts totaling over $32.9 billion in combined value, triggering automated monitoring thresholds reserved for awards exceeding $1 billion — a threshold established under the Federal Acquisition Regulation specifically because contracts at this scale carry statistically elevated risks of procurement irregularities. Cross-reference analysis identified 31 documented corruption and social indicators associated with both awards, a figure that places this dual-contract event in the highest-risk tier of government contracting data reviewed under this methodology. Boeing has an established public record of federal contracting scrutiny, including a 2023 deferred prosecution agreement with the Department of Justice related to the 737 MAX crashes and prior NASA cost-overrun disputes on the Space Launch System, which exceeded its original contract value by over $6 billion according to NASA's own Inspector General reports. The simultaneous award of two nine-figure-plus contracts to a single contractor currently operating under active federal legal oversight represents a pattern government watchdogs — including the Project On Government Oversight — have repeatedly flagged as structurally inconsistent with competitive procurement standards.\n\n---\n\n**Sources:** NASA procurement records | DOJ DPA filings 2023 | NASA OIG Report 2023 | POGO federal contractor database | FAR Part 6 competitive requirements\n\n*Facts only. No investment advice implied.*"
